The HIK project consists of multiple components, each with its own license.

- The core kernel (src/Core-0) is licensed under **GPL-2.0-only** with the
  **HIK-service-exception**. This exception allows Privileged-1 services
  to be distributed under any license terms.  
  See `LICENSES/GPL-2.0-only` and `LICENSES/exception/HIK-service-exception`.

- Privileged-1 services (src/Privileged-1) are licensed under **MPL-2.0**.  
  See `LICENSES/MPL-2.0`.

- User-space components (src/Application-3) are licensed under **Apache-2.0**.  
  See `LICENSES/Apache-2.0`.

- The bootloader (src/bootloader) is licensed under **MIT**.  
  See `LICENSES/MIT`.

- Build scripts (scripts/) are licensed under **Apache-2.0**.  
  See `LICENSES/Apache-2.0`.

- Documentation (docs/) is licensed under **CC-BY-4.0**.  
  See `LICENSES/CC-BY-4.0`.

- Other files (e.g., README.md, CONTRIBUTING.md, Makefile, *.sh, and any
  files not covered above) are licensed under **MIT**.  
  See `LICENSES/MIT`.

